value.value: 体重異常
anomaly in average weight compared to controls
体重の増加
greater than normal average weight
肥満
a status with body weight that is grossly above the average, acceptable or desirable weight, usually due to accumulation of excess fat tissue in the body
体重減少
lower than normal average weight
体重減少
progressive reduction of body weight below normal average for age

definition.value: This term should be used when weight is lost in the absence of external interventions.

value.value: 体サイズの増加
larger than average body weight, height and/or length of an organism compared to controls
体サイズの減少
smaller than average body weight, height and/or length of an organism compared to controls
胸部の巨大化
wider diameter, or distended chest cavity
樽状胸
distended circumference of the thoracic and abdominal areas
腹部拡張
abdomen appears curved outward or swollen
転移能増加
greater likelihood of a tumor cell spreading from the site of the initial tumor formation and forming a secondary tumor at another site not directly connected with it
転移能減少
reduced likelihood of a tumor cell spreading from the site of the initial tumor formation and forming a secondary tumor at another site not directly connected with it
巻き毛の感覚毛
coiled or spiral shape of the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors
もつれた感覚毛
snarled or intertwined stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors
よじれた感覚毛
sharp bends in the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors
波状の感覚毛
undulations or a sinusoidal shape of the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors
感覚毛損失
inability to retain the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors
感覚毛の伸長
longer average length of the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors
感覚毛の短縮
decreased length of the stiff hairs projecting from the face around the nose of most mammals which act as touch receptors
低密度な感覚毛
few and widely spaced stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors
感覚毛の欠如
absence of the stiff hairs that project from the face around the nose of most mammals, and which act as touch receptors
眼の発生異常
malformation or arrest of differentiation of the visual organ
水晶体誘導の異常
any anomaly in the signaling at short range between the head ectoderm and the optic vesicle that results in the head ectoderm forming a lens
硝子体毛細血管系の残留
failure of the degeneration of the transient vascular system of the eye during development, that normally nourishes the retina, immature lens and primary vitreous of the developing eye
眼瞼開口の遅延
late average time for the first postnatal eye opening

definition.value: In mouse, eyelids normally fuse about 5 days prior to birth and reopen about 19 days later.

value.value: 水晶体小胞の発生異常
malformation or abnormal patterning of the ectodermal invagination that forms opposite the optic cup in the primordium of the lens of the eye
無眼球症

absence of the globe and ocular tissue from the orbit, with or without the presence of ocular adnexa (eyelids, conjunctiva, and lacrimal apparatus); remnants of the globe sometimes appear in ectopic locations
巨大眼球症
increased average size of the eyes
小眼球症
reduced average size of one or both eyes; generally refers to a congenital defect
両眼間距離/位置の異常
abnormal placement of the eyes in relation to each other or in relation to other craniofacial structures
両眼隔離症
increased interpupillary distance, i.e. increased distance between the center of the pupils of the two eyes
出生時眼瞼開口

open eyes instead of closed at perinatal stage; failure of the upper and lower thin folds of skin and muscle that cover the exposed portion of the eye to fuse completely together during development and an individual is born with the eye(s) uncovered leading to degrees of injury and blindness

definition.value: In mouse, eyelids normally fuse about 5 days prior to birth and reopen about 19 days later.

value.value: 水晶体の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays
白内障
complete or partial opacity of the lens
水晶体の巨大化
increased size of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays
水晶体の矮小化
reduced size of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays
角膜と水晶体の癒着

condition in which the transparent anterior portion of the fibrous coat of the eye is joined to the transparent biconvex cellular refractive structure lying between the iris and vitreous humor of the eye
水晶体の極性異常
failure of normal orientation of the lens during development
眼水晶体線維水腫
swollen cortical fibers of the eye lens
結膜の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the mucous membrane that lines the inner surface of the eyelids and the front of the eyeball
角膜の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the transparent anterior portion of the fibrous coat of the eye that covers the iris, pupil, and anterior chamber; together with the lens, the cornea refracts light
角膜炎発生率の上昇
greater than average occurrence and/or persistence of the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the cornea
角膜混濁
complete or partial clouding of the cornea
角膜の瘢痕
appearance of fibrous tissue on the cornea after healing in response to injury
瞳孔の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the central circular aperture of the iris through which light rays enter the eye
瞳孔混濁
milky or cloudy appearance of the central circular aperture of the iris through which light rays normally enter the eye
瞳孔の形態異常
shape defects in the aperture of the iris through which light rays enter the eye, usually circular
瞳孔の矮小化
smaller than normal size of the central circular aperture of the iris through which light rays enter the eye
虹彩の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the adjustable membrane, composed of the stroma and pigmented epithelium, located just in front of the crystalline lens within the eye
眼の色素沈着異常
change in the normal pigmentation of the eye to another color, or lack of color
